## Non-Negotiable Rules

1. Dependency Rule: core/ has ZERO outward imports
2. No `Final[]` annotations — use `_UPPER_SNAKE_CASE` for internal constants
3. Module-level docstrings on every Python file
4. `raise ... from e` for exception chaining
5. No raw SQL — use ORM exclusively
6. No `Any` type hints — use `object` as fallback
7. Registry-first: constants live in `naming_registry.json`
8. Structured logging only (structlog, `%s` formatting)
9. Shell scripts use `.zsh` extension exclusively
10. Conventional Commits enforced on all commits
